# File Organization

Keep each file focused on a single concern.

## UI components: one component per file

A `.tsx` file exports **one** UI component (plus its `Props` type). Sub-pieces that exist only as render helpers live in their own file under the same folder.

```
src/app/auth/ui/settings/
  SignInMethodsPanel.tsx        # the panel
  PasskeyRow.tsx                # extracted row, not inlined
  ConnectedIdentityRow.tsx      # ditto
```

- ❌ Don't define `const PasskeyRow = (...) => <li>...</li>` inside `SignInMethodsPanel.tsx` to "save a file".
- ✅ Do extract once a sub-element has its own state, more than ~30 lines of JSX, or is reused by a sibling.

## Helpers: not in component files

Pure functions, formatters, type guards, and constants must not live in a component file. Move them to a sibling helper module so they're testable and importable.

```
src/app/auth/ui/settings/
  SignInMethodsPanel.tsx
  format.ts                     # formatLastUsed, dateFormatter
  providers.ts                  # providerMeta(id)
```

```typescript
// ❌ BAD: helpers in the component file
// src/app/auth/ui/settings/SignInMethodsPanel.tsx
const formatLastUsed = (when: Date | null): string => { /* ... */ };
const providerMeta = (id: string) => OAUTH_PROVIDERS.find(...) ?? { ... };

export const SignInMethodsPanel = (...) => { ... };
```

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: helpers in a sibling file
// src/app/auth/ui/settings/format.ts
export const formatLastUsed = (when: Date | null): string => { /* ... */ };

// src/app/auth/ui/settings/SignInMethodsPanel.tsx
import { formatLastUsed } from './format';
```

## Where helpers belong

- **Pure logic / domain rules** → `src/app/<feature>/domain/` (e.g. `webauthn.ts`)
- **Server-only data fetchers** → `src/framework/<area>/` (mark with `import 'server-only'`)
- **Cross-feature utilities** → `src/lib/`
- **Feature-local UI helpers (formatters, icon pickers)** → sibling file in the same `ui/` folder

## Custom hooks

Each `useXxx` hook lives in its own file under `src/app/<feature>/domain/` or a `hooks/` folder — never inlined above a component.
